orted operations, implementing a fallback test wrapped in a try-catch for errors and checked exceptions.\\n\\nI’m also considering how the classloader hierarchy affects things, especially since the parent already has `org.gradle.wrapper.Download`. It seems like inner classes and potential IDownload implementations might need to load in a specific order. Plus, it looks like I’ll have to handle Base64 loading and URLStreamHandler considerations carefully as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Setting Up HTTP Handler for Tests**\\n\\nFor the first test, I plan to use a HEAD handler. The HttpServer should handle HEAD requests correctly, but it won’t write a response body. In the `sendHeadRequest` method for Basic Auth, I'll need to ensure `addBasicAuth` is called before connecting, using the user info from the URI. I think I should also put in an assertion to verify that everything is functioning as expected. This way, I'm covering all my bases and keeping things organized.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring modular support**\\n\\nI'm considering using `com.sun.net.httpserver` in a modular context. It seems like it should work, but I’m pondering whether native image support is in play here. I might need to add `--add-modules jdk.httpserver` during the configuration. Also, it could be helpful to review existing tests for any insights or confirmations. I need to search for more information to clarify how to proceed effectively!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MWZjNelB0uUcMZjaaiyJGAcM|fc_003b1cf61275cb60016a4256f3020c81968893f7ba0a49591f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"com.sun.net.httpserver\" tests/src -g '*.java' | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1265, "output": 1117, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36174, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 17