es**\\n\\nI'm looking into a potential issue with `getHostString` where the loopback may return either 127.0.0.1 or a hostname. It's valid to have a URI here, but if IPv6 is involved, then it needs brackets for `0:0:...:1`. Typically, `InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress()` returns \\\"localhost/127.0.0.1\\\". If I specify \\\"127.0.0.1\\\" explicitly, that could avoid any ambiguity with IPv6. \\n\\nAdditionally, I need to make sure that the Basic Auth header value has a space after \\\"Basic\\\". I might need to check for any trailing spaces that could affect this. Lastly, if there's an `InvocationTargetException`, I need to ensure it's clear what exceptions are thrown and if there's a dependency in `build.gradle` for `javax.xml.bind`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test needs**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I really need to run any tests right now. It seems like I should mention that tests won’t be run due to the instructions. I should double-check the changes in the git diff to make sure everything looks good before moving on. It’s always better to be thorough, right? I'll just want to ensure clarity on why testing isn't necessary at this moment.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_R1arCK86Zbq1OJUApqCBQ7JR|fc_003b1cf61275cb60016a425723f0908196bc8966baedc4992a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-gradle-resolver/3.33.1/build.gradle tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-gradle-resolver/3.33.1/src/test/java/io_quarkus/quarkus_bootstrap_gradle_resolver/OrgGradleWrapperDownloadTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1741, "output": 1145, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42310, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782732559989, "responseId": "resp_003b1cf61275cb60016a42571081dc819683af3963e0d298cf"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "